      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This FD3S chassis remains a benchmark in balanced engineering, featuring the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary powerplant. The engine pulls strongly through both boost transitions, benefiting from a recently refreshed vacuum line simplified setup and verified compression across both rotors. Handling is sharp and communicative, thanks to the factory double-wishbone suspension and a responsive Torsen limited-slip differential. The exterior retains its iconic lines with minor patina consistent with a well-loved driver, while the interior remains driver-centric and functional. This is a mechanically honest example of 90s JDM performance, perfect for the enthusiast who values turn-key dynamics and chassis rigidity over concours perfection.",
